
{center}
{subhead} joeCARD goes AMIGA{def}
{left}
{p} {p}

Met@box - joeCARD & littleJoe | joeCARD goes AMIGA
{p} {p}
Hildesheim/ Germany, March 26, 1999{p}
JoeCard G3 goes AMIGA !
{p} {p}
met@box AG (formerly known as PIOS Computer AG) is proud to announce the
newest member of it´s award-winning JoeCard family:  the AmiJOE.
{p} {p}
The AmiJOE will be the first pure PowerPC solution for the existing Amiga
platform.  AmiJOE will implement the powerful G3 PowerPC architecture which
will enable the Amiga to outperform today´s personal computers.  The
met@box engineering team decided to make the AmiJOE available not only to
users of the high end Amiga Systems, but also to the many people being
committed to their A 1200.  The basic specifications of the AmiJOE products
are:
{p} {p}
 PowerPC750 (Lonestar) G3 Processor{p}
 333 or 400 MHz{p}
 1.024Kbyte Backside Cache{p}
 66  MHz Local Bus Speed (A 1200){p}
 100 MHz Local Bus Speed (A 2000/ A 3000/ A 4000){p}
 UniversalSerial Bus (USB){p}
 RealtimeClock (RTC) (A 1200 only){p}
 PCI compatible Connector for future expansion (A 2000/ A 3000/ A4000 only){p}
 Socketfür SDRAM Modules{p}
 FlashROM for easy Software upgrade
{p} {p}
The AmiJOE for the A 1200 is clocked at 333 Mhz at a recommended street
price of 599 EUR, while the AmiJOE for the A 2000/ A 3000/ A 4000 is
clocked at 400 Mhz with a recommended street price of 899 EUR.  Prices do
not include VAT/MWSt.
{p} {p}
met@box AG is ready to take orders without any prepayments.  First product
shipments are planned for the beginning of Q3 1999.  Purchase orders please
send to {bold}sales@joecard.com{nobold}
{p} {p}
